### Expense Approval Pipeline - Version B (Logic Apps + Service Bus) test scenarios
###
### The Logic App is triggered by a message arriving in the `expense-requests`
### Service Bus queue. These requests send messages via the Service Bus REST API.
### Replace the @sb_* variables with your namespace values.
###
### Alternative: use Service Bus Explorer in the Azure portal to send the same JSON
### bodies to the queue and capture screenshots of the Logic App runs.

@sb_namespace = YOUR_SB_NAMESPACE
@queue = expense-requests
@sas_token = SharedAccessSignature sr=...&sig=...&se=...&skn=RootManageSharedAccessKey
@validate_fn = https://YOUR_FUNCTIONAPP.azurewebsites.net/api/validate-expense?code=YOUR_FUNCTION_KEY

### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
### Smoke test: call validation Function directly (outside Logic App)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{validate_fn}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Alice Johnson",
  "employee_email": "alice@example.com",
  "amount": 42.50,
  "category": "supplies",
  "description": "USB-C hub",
  "manager_email": "bob.manager@example.com"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
### 1. Valid expense under $100 -> auto-approved
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
POST https://{{sb_namespace}}.servicebus.windows.net/{{queue}}/messages
Authorization: {{sas_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Alice Johnson",
  "employee_email": "alice@example.com",
  "amount": 42.50,
  "category": "supplies",
  "description": "USB-C hub for new laptop",
  "manager_email": "bob.manager@example.com"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2. Valid expense >= $100, manager approves (click link in email)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
POST https://{{sb_namespace}}.servicebus.windows.net/{{queue}}/messages
Authorization: {{sas_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Alice Johnson",
  "employee_email": "alice@example.com",
  "amount": 450.00,
  "category": "travel",
  "description": "Taxi + conference registration",
  "manager_email": "bob.manager@example.com"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
### 3. Valid expense >= $100, manager rejects
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
POST https://{{sb_namespace}}.servicebus.windows.net/{{queue}}/messages
Authorization: {{sas_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Charlie Davis",
  "employee_email": "charlie@example.com",
  "amount": 2500.00,
  "category": "equipment",
  "description": "Second 4K monitor",
  "manager_email": "bob.manager@example.com"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
### 4. Valid expense >= $100, no manager response -> escalated (timeout)
###    Do not click either link. Wait for the HTTP webhook action timeout.
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
POST https://{{sb_namespace}}.servicebus.windows.net/{{queue}}/messages
Authorization: {{sas_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Dana Kim",
  "employee_email": "dana@example.com",
  "amount": 199.99,
  "category": "software",
  "description": "Annual JetBrains license",
  "manager_email": "bob.manager@example.com"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
### 5. Missing required fields -> validation error
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
POST https://{{sb_namespace}}.servicebus.windows.net/{{queue}}/messages
Authorization: {{sas_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Eve Lee",
  "amount": 75.00,
  "category": "meals"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
### 6. Invalid category -> validation error
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------
POST https://{{sb_namespace}}.servicebus.windows.net/{{queue}}/messages
Authorization: {{sas_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Frank Wu",
  "employee_email": "frank@example.com",
  "amount": 30.00,
  "category": "gambling",
  "description": "Team building",
  "manager_email": "bob.manager@example.com"
}
